Greetings to President of Guinea-Bissau 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Monday sent a message of greetings to Joao Bernardo Vieira, President of the Republic of Guinea-Bissau, on the occasion of the 35th anniversary of its proclamation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim in the message wholeheartedly wished the President bigger success in his responsible work for peace, stability and socio-economic development of the country.

Congratulations to New Thai PM 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- Premier of the DPRK Cabinet Kim Yong Il on Sept. 19 sent a congratulatory message to Somchai Wongsawat on his election as Prime Minister of Thailand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message sincerely wished him success in his noble work for the stability and development of the country.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Nepalese Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, had a friendly talk with the Nepalese government information delegation headed by Krishna Bahadur Mahara, minister of Information and Communications of Nepal, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Minister of Culture Kang Nung Su who is chairman of the DPRK Information Committee and other officials concerned.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Head of Nepalese Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the head of the Nepalese government information delegation on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was handed to Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, by Krishna Bahadur Mahara, minister of Information and Communications of Nepal who is leading the delegation, on Tuesday.

Kim Jong Gak Meets Delegation of Senior Political Officers of VPA 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Gak, first vice-director of the General Political Department of the Korean People's Army, met and had a friendly talk with the delegation of senior political officers of the Vietnam People's Army led by Le Van Dung, secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam and head of the VPA General Political Department, on Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Col. General of the KPA Sim Sang Dae, Vietnamese Ambassador to the DPRK Le Van Cu and Military Attache of the embassy Dau Xuan Long.

Foreign Delegations Here 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- A delegation of senior political officers of the Vietnam People's Army led by Le Van Dung, secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam and head of the VPA General Political Department, arrived here today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A function welcoming the delegation took place in front of the Monument to Victory in the Fatherland Liberation War on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Jong Gak, first vice-director of the General Political Department of the Korean People's Army, general officers including Col. General Sim Sang Dae and officers of the KPA and Vietnamese Ambassador to the DPRK Le Van Cu and Military Attache Dau Xuan Long. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Arrivals on the same day included a delegation of the Socialist Party of Romania led by Vasile Orleanu, chairman of the Supreme Council of the party, and a Cuban government economic delegation.

Delegation of Senior Political Officers of VPA Feted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- The General Political Department of the Korean People's Army hosted a banquet in honor of the visiting delegation of senor political officers of the Vietnam People's Army on Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were the members of the delegation led by Le Van Dung, secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam and head of the VPA General Political Department, Le Van Cu, Vietnamese ambassador to the DPRK, and Dau Xuan Long, military attache of the embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Jong Gak, first vice-director of the General Political Department of the KPA, general officers including Col. General Sim Sang Dae and officers of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Gak in a speech made at the banquet recalled the fact that the friendly relations between the DPRK and Vietnam provided by President Kim Il Sung and President Ho Chi Minh have grown strong under the care of General Secretary Kim Jong Il and General Secretary Nong Duc Manh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the invariable stand of the DPRK to steadily develop the relations of friendship and cooperation between the two armies, he said, expressing the belief that the delegation's visit to the DPRK would provide a significant occasion in boosting the traditional friendly and cooperative relations between the two armies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Le Van Dung in a speech said that the armies and peoples of Vietnam and the DPRK have fought against their common enemy and defended socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He referred to the fact that the KPA has achieved great successes in the struggle to defend the country and accomplish the cause of socialism under the leadership of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The party, government, army and people of Vietnam feel thankful to their DPRK counterparts for rendering support, material and moral, to the Vietnam anti-U.S. war of resistance for national salvation, he noted, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He would make positive efforts to steadily consolidate the friendly relations between Vietnam and the DPRK provided by the leaders of the two countries.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Head of Delegation of Senior Political Officers of VPA 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the head of the delegation of senior political officers of the Vietnam People's Army on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was handed on Tuesday to Kim Jong Gak, first vice-director of the General Political Department of the Korean People's Army, by Le Van Dung, secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam and head of the VPA General Political Department, who is leading the delegation.

Folding Screen Relics Exhibition
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- An exhibition of folding screen relics is now open at the Korean Folklore Museum in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display are folding screens belonging to the period of the Ri Dynasty (1392-1910). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than forty pieces of relics on show are divided into picture, embroidery and calligraphy folding screens, which show well traditional living customs, distinguished painting art, calligraphy and embroidery techniques of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such picture folding screens as screens depicting ten long-living animals and things, cranes and pine trees, flowers and birds, and landscape represent beautiful natural scenery and simple dreams of the forefathers to live long in harmony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bamboo folding screens depict in bold style the strong will of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The embroidery folding screen of flowers and birds which was used at wedding ceremonies and the embroidery folding screen of rural life depicting the diligent working life of peasants in four seasons give glimpses of the talent of the then artists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also displayed are handwriting screens. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The visitors are deeply impressed by the folding screen relics which vividly reflect the creative wisdom and emotional life of the Koreans.

National Martial Arts Championships Close
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- The 3rd national martial arts championships for September 10 Cup closed on Tuesday with due ceremony at the Taekwon-Do Hall. The championships were opened on Sept. 18. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the championships the Pyongyang City Taekwon-Do players team placed first in the total standings of Taekwon-Do, Korean wrestling and go events, the North Hwanghae Provincial Taekwon-Do players team second and the South Hamgyong Provincial Taekwon-Do players team third. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending the closing ceremony were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and officials concerned, players and school youth and children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cup and medals were awarded to the teams and players who proved successful. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hwang Pong Yong, chairman of the Korean Taekwon-Do Committee, made a closing address.

Danger of Military Exercises of U.S. and S. Korean Puppet Armed Forces Flailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- Leading newspapers today carry a military commentator's article disclosing the dangerous nature of the reckless war exercises of the U.S. imperialists and the south Korean puppet armed forces which may lead to confrontation and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Terming the military exercises now under way in and around south Korea a direct product of the U.S. imperialists' unchanged policy to stifle the DPRK and the Lee Myung Bak group's policy for confrontation with it, the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As already disclosed, the U.S. imperialists' policy of aggression calls for turning the world into a "pan-American world" in which U.S.-style democracy prevails and the U.S.-style market economic system dominates. The present Bush administration's policy to stifle the DPRK is based on this policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a matter of fact, the U.S. promises a peaceful and negotiated settlement at talks but seems to be keenly interested in unhesitatingly breaking the promise and exercising "the strength of the U.S. without limit" behind the scene, pursuant to this policy of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Traitor Lee Myung Bak's new policy for confrontation with the DPRK is a replica of the above-said policy of aggression of the U.S., his master. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He is uttering sugar-coated words, calling fellow countrymen in the north those the south should get reconciled and cooperate with while talking about "co-existence and co-prosperity." But behind the scene, he is crying out for the policy of confrontation with the north and the theory of war of aggression against it after labeling the fellow countrymen in the north "principal enemy." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a natural result of this policy that the traitor steeped in the bitterness toward the DPRK to the marrow of his bones has become frantic recently in saber-rattling targeted against fellow countrymen while egging the puppet Defense Ministry on to justify the policies pursued by the successive military dictatorial regimes as ones that "checked the activities of pro-north leftist forces" and "contributed to the modernization of the nation".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unending war exercises are, in all aspects, a product of the policy of aggression and the theory of war against the DPRK pursued by the master and the servant, and an open racket of military confrontation aimed at "tightening south Korea-U.S. alliance."
 Herein lies the danger of the saber-rattling staged by the U.S. imperialists and the south Korean puppets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military maneuvers being staged in and around south Korea are part of the master and the servant's war preparations aimed at finally examining the feasibility of the already rounded off strategy and operational plan for aggression on the DPRK in direction of tightening the "alliance." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' strategy for a war of aggression on the DPRK has been perfectly rounded off after undergoing several phases of amendment and supplementation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This war strategy precisely means a "strategy for a preemptive attack" and a "shock and awe strategy" veiled with "prevention strategy" which had already been applied on a trial basis to other countries including Iraq for the aggression of them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists and the south Korean puppets have carefully worked out detailed operational plans to swallow up the DPRK according to this strategy with various situations into due consideration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the war exercises that have escalated going beyond the tolerance limit in south Korea since Lee Myung Bak came to power are aimed to reexamine the feasibility of all the operational plans and enhance the joint and combined operational capabilities of the U.S. imperialist aggression troops and units of the puppet forces based on them and finally round off the overall preparations for a war of aggression now that the "issue of tightening the alliance" is high on the agenda. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Herein lies greater danger of the saber-rattling of the U.S. imperialists and the puppets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said war exercises now under way in and around south Korea are the maneuvers staged under the simulated conditions of an actual war with huge U.S. aggression troops and three services of the south Korean puppet armed forces as well as various type nuclear strike means involved under the pretext of "tightening the alliance" for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is none other than the heinous U.S. imperialists and the Lee group who are openly pursuing the hostile policy toward the DPRK while pressurizing the DPRK to dismantle its nuclear weapons unilaterally after throwing away the agreement of the six-party talks and even the principle of "action for action" based on it recognized by the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are mobilizing huge aggression troops and shipping various type nuclear strike means, timed to coincide with such moves, in a bid to make a nuclear war to be launched by them an established fact. This betrays even greater danger of their war exercises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All these moves go to clearly prove that the ruckus of "tightened alliance" and war exercises being staged by Lee together with his American master are an act of evidently swimming against the trend of the times and an outright challenge to the desire and demand of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an unpardonable traitorous and anti-peace action to continue staging dangerous war exercises under the pretext of "threat" from someone and "security", still seized with the concept of confrontation dating back to the Cold War era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Aggressors are bound to meet merciless punishment by the army of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists and traitor Lee Myung Bak would be well advised to clearly understand that all DPRK-targeted war exercises aimed at "tightened alliance" are hideous and traitorous crimes going against reunification and peace as they quell all the Koreans' desires and wishes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lee should bear in mind that if all the people are killed and the whole territory turns into a debris due to confrontation and war, Lee himself will not be able to survive, much less achieving "co-existence and co-prosperity" so much touted by him.

S. Korean Warmongers' Distortion of History under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- The Lee Myung Bak group will have to pay dearly for the reckless anti-DPRK confrontation racket aimed at blocking the north-south reconciliation and unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday warns this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accusing the south Korean puppet military of working hard with bloodshot eyes to fan up confrontation with the DPRK, the commentary notes: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is evidenced by the fact that the south Korean "Ministry of National Defence" submitted a "25-point proposal" for revising history textbooks for high schools to the "Ministry of Education, Science and Technology" under the pretext of strengthening "anti-communist and security education," claiming that "leftist tendency" was observed in some history textbooks. What should not to be overlooked is the fact that the puppet military malignantly slandered the system of the DPRK.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean military group seeks to whitewash the crime-woven history of fascist rule enforced by the erstwhile dictatorial regimes, characterized by sycophancy towards the U.S., treachery, mass killings of patriotic people and hideous human rights abuses, and advertise the fascist rule as "an unavoidable measure taken against the north." They have gone the lengths of kicking up a racket of confrontation, defaming even the political system of the dignified DPRK. This is touching off irrepressible resentment among the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean puppet military's reckless actions are a grave politically motivated provocation to the DPRK and traitorous criminal acts to stir up atmosphere of confrontation with the DPRK in south Korean society and drive the inter-Korean relations into uncontrollable bankruptcy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The puppet military has nothing to do with the issue of history textbooks for high schools in south Korea. Nevertheless, it is keen to meddle in this issue and retrogressively revise the textbooks, linking them with the DPRK. This brings to light the treacherous nature of the puppet military hell-bent on confrontation with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now that traitor Lee Myung Bak is sticking to the policy of confrontation with the DPRK veiled with the watchword of "pragmatism," it is obvious that his underlings are not in a position to say anything different from his words and all the "government" officials have no option but to pursue reactionary conservatism and confrontation with the DPRK.

Japan's Moves for Reinvasion under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- The Japanese government in its recently-released "2008 defence white paper" absurdly claimed that the DPRK poses a "serious threat" to Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this regard, Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed commentary says that the real threat is Japan's moves for overseas expansion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has been exposed to the constant threat from the U.S. and its allies such as Japan which blindly follows it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's real threat to the DPRK finds its vivid manifestation in the fact that the Japanese government in its "defence white paper" described Tok Islet of Korea as part of Japan's territory again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This action is nothing but a renewed declaration of reinvasion of Korea. Acting upon the above-said scenario for territorial expansion, ships of Japan's Maritime "Self-Defence Force" are now keen to intrude into and occupy the islet, thus rendering the situation in the East Sea of Korea tense. This clearly indicates who is posing threat and who is exposed to threat as far as the relations between the DPRK and Japan are concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese government emphasized the need to institute a "permanent law" for dispatching the SDF overseas in the "defence white paper". It is aimed to justify its military aggression of any part of the world any time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's evermore frantic moves to stifle the DPRK in conspiracy with the U.S. would only heighten the vigilance and resentment at Japan among the Korean people and compel them to bolster up their armed forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan would be well advised to stop its foolish moves for reinvasion.

U.S. Branded as Destroyer of World Peace and Security
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- The U.S. should admit crimes it has committed as the world's worst spreader of WMDs, chieftain of sparking off arms race and wrecker of peace, and face stern punishment by mankind, says Minju Joson today in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. talks rubbish that its policy of arms sale helps "strengthen the cooperative relations for security" and "increase the capability for carrying out joint military operations," but it is sheer sophism aimed at veiling its black-hearted intention, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. policy of exporting weapons overseas serves as a catalyst sparking off armed conflicts and arms race by threatening peace and security and upsetting balance of forces in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has long pursued the unilateral policy of arms sale to Israel under the pretext of "ensuring security of allies" and thus put the military strength of Israel on a considerable level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A serious imbalance of forces standing in confrontation, with Israel on one side and the Arab countries on the other side, compelled the Arab countries to feel the need to increase their own military capability and this turned the Middle East region into a big market for arms sale. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. rakes up big profits every year by sparking off arms race after rendering the situation in the major dispute-torn regions of the world extremely tense and deliberately creating the demand for weapons through massive arms sale to those regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, it brands some countries as "dangerous spreaders of WMDs", a shameless act reminding one of a thief crying "stop the thief." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With nothing can the U.S. evade the responsibility for making the world unsafe and the mankind miserable.

Grand Festival of Koreans in Japan Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- A grand festival of Koreans in Japan was held with splendor in Tokyo on Sunday to celebrate the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending the opening ceremony were more than 20,000 Koreans in Japan from all walks of life including officials of the organizations of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) in Tokyo and local areas of Japan, Japan-resident Koreans of the first generation who have contributed to the patriotic movement, those of merit and aged compatriots and the compatriots of "the South Korean Residents Association in Japan" and independent Koreans whom Chongryon found out and got in touch with through the "movement to invite Koreans in Japan to come to the fold of Chongryon".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ho Jong Man, chief vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon who is vice-chairman of the Executive Committee of the above-said festival, made an opening address. He said that there are many countries in the world but the state founded by President Kim Il Sung and led by Kim Jong Il is the only glorious and dignified country that has 60-year-long history of victory and glory and has demonstrated before the whole world the might of independence in politics, self-support in the economy and self-reliance in national defence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the grand festival was declared open, 2,012 balloons were released to fly amid the display of fireworks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koreans of the first generation including officials of Chongryon in Kanto and advisors to the Union of Democratic Korean Women in Japan and Koreans of the second, third and fourth generations, successors to the patriotic cause, more than 1,200 all told, sang in chorus the "Song of the Proclamation of the People's Republic".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Introduced there were video letters from people in the homeland and prominent figures of different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed art performance "Prosperous Homeland and Happiness of Compatriots".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the performance, the 3rd "Central Contest in Singing Korean Songs" took place. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Photo exhibitions under the titles "Glorious History of Juche Korea, Six Decades of Great Changes" and "60 Years of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan under the Banner of the Republic" were held. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, colorful events celebrating the 60th birthday of the DPRK took place at the Korean Cultural Hall in Tokyo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There opened the "3rd Central Contest in Peasants Dancing and Singing" and the "Sept. 9 Tournament of Masters at Go" participated in by compatriots of different headquarters and branches of Chongryon and students of schools at various levels. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "Sept. 9 Central Korean Wrestling Contest of Strong Koreans in Japan", in which the wrestlers selected from different organizations and schools in Kanto participated, added to the festive atmosphere. The children's plaza was alive with sports and amusement games of children. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the Union of Democratic Korean Women in Japan, the Korean Youth League in Japan and other organizations in different areas were busy serving participants.

DPRK's Diamond Jubilee Marked Abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- Receptions, photo exhibitions, friendly meetings, round-table talks and other events took place at the DPRK missions in Vietnam, Syria, Pakistan, Nepal, Bangladesh, Malaysia, Kuwait, Guinea, Nigeria, United Kingdom, France, Poland, Bulgaria, Austria and the DPRK Permanent Mission at the UN from Sept. 4 to 9 to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venues of the functions were famous works of the peerlessly great persons, photos showing their glorious revolutionary histories and immortal feats and books and photos introducing the course of victory and glory covered by the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the functions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Vietnamese deputy prime minister and foreign minister said that the Vietnamese people rejoice over the victories achieved by the DPRK over the past six decades and have always supported the Korean people's cause of building and developing the country with deep concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A senior official of Bangladesh said that they are pleased to note that peace and security are preserved in the Korean Peninsula and the rest of Northeast Asia thanks to the outstanding Songun politics of General Secretary Kim Jong Il and the DPRK is shedding its rays all over the world as a politically and ideologically strong nation and a military power which even the imperialist allied forces dare not provoke. And he hoped that Korea would be reunified peacefully in the interests of all the Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Great Britain (Marxist-Leninist) noted that the Korean people have made a dynamic advance under the wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. The moves of the U.S.-led imperialists to stifle socialism in Korea are bound to meet a fiasco, he said.

60th Birthday of DPRK Marked in Czech Republic
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- A DPRK book, photo and handicraft exhibition was opened with due ceremony in Pribram County of the Czech Republic on Sept. 11 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venue of the exhibition were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il, photographs dealing with their immortal exploits and introducing Songun Korea and handicrafts associated with the wisdom and skills of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairwoman of the Prague City Committee of the Communist Party of Czech and Moravia expressed belief that the exhibition would help deepen the understanding between the two peoples and boost the friendly relations between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Pribram County Committee of the party noted that the 60-year-long history of the DPRK is a history of creation and construction in which the Korean people have dynamically advanced socialism despite all ordeals and difficulties under the wise leadership of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also a glorious history in which the Korean people have emerged victorious thanks to Songun, frustrating the challenges of the U.S.-led imperialists and their moves to stifle the DPRK, he said, stressing that the Korean people's cause of socialism and national reunification is sure to triumph under the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il.

DPRK Felicitated on Its Diamond Jubilee
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 23 (KCNA) -- Marwan Sudah, chairman of the Arab Committee for Solidarity with Korean People and Supporting the Reunification of Korea in Jordan, issued a statement on September 9 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said in the statement that the DPRK is the country which realized the desire of President Kim Il Sung who devoted all his life to providing a just and equal society to the Korean people and the world oppressed people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world progressive people boundlessly revere and highly praise Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il for having performed immortal exploits to shine long in history, he noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people have successfully built a socialist state fully ready for either peace or war and secured war deterrent strong enough to frustrate the moves of the U.S. imperialists and their followers for aggression and firmly defend the revolutionary gains. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that world-startling achievements have been made in Korea over the past years under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, the statement expressed conviction that the DPRK would further prosper as it is making a dynamic advance, holding aloft the banner of the Juche idea and Songun under his wise leadership.

Kim Jong Il recibe presente del jefe de delegacion de Nepal
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 23 de septiembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il recibio presente que le dedicara el jefe de la delegacion de informacion gubernamental de Nepal, de visita en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El ministro de Informacion y Comunicaciones, Krishna Bahadur Mahara, quien preside la delegacion, lo entrego este martes al presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Kim Yong Nam.

Actos en representaciones coreanas por dia de fundacion de RPDC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 23 de septiembre (ATCC) -- Con motivo del 60o aniversario de la fundacion de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, tuvieron lugar del dia 4 al 9 banquetes, exposiciones de fotos, encuentros de amistad, charlas y otros actos en las representaciones coreanas acreditadas en Vietnam, Siria, Pakistan, Nepal, Bangladesh, Malasia, Kuwait, Guinea, Nigeria, Gran Bretana, Francia, Polonia, Bulgaria y Austria y en la representacion permanente de la RPDC ante la ONU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En los lugares de actos estaban exhibidos las obras maestras de los grandes hombres simpares y las fotos alusivas a sus historias revolucionarias llenas de gloria y a sus hazanas inmortales y los libros y fotos que dan a conocer la trayectoria victoriosa y gloriosa de la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En las ocasiones hubo discursos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El viceprimer ministro y ministro de Relaciones Exteriores del gobierno de Vietnam dijo que el pueblo vietnamita se regocija de las victorias logradas por la RPDC durante los 60 anos pasados y apoya invariablemente con profunda atencion la causa del pueblo coreano por la construccion y el desarrollo del pais. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Un funcionario de alto rango de Bangladesh expreso su alegria de que gracias a la destacada politica del Songun (priorizacion militar) de Su Excelencia    Kim Jong Il, se defienden la paz y la seguridad de la Peninsula Coreana y del Nordeste Asiatico y Corea esparce a todo el mundo sus brillos como potencia ideo-politica y militar a que no se atreven a atacar las fuerzas aliadas imperialistas y deseo que la reunificacion de Corea se logre por via pacifica conforme al interes de toda la nacion coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El presidente del Comite Central del Partido Comunista (Marxista-Leninista) de Gran Bretana  senalo que el pueblo coreano ha avanzado a pasos firmes bajo la sabia direccion del gran Presidente Kim Il Sung y Su Excelencia Kim Jong Il y afirmo que no podran evitar el fracaso las maniobras de los imperialistas encabezados por EE.UU. tendentes a aplastar el socialismo de Corea.
